5|$|The September 1944 Hyde Park Agreement {{extended}} both {{commercial and}} military cooperation into the post-war period. The Quebec Agreement specified that nuclear weapons {{would not be}} used against another country without mutual consent. On 4 July 1945, Wilson agreed that the <b>use</b> <b>of</b> <b>nuclear</b> weapons against Japan would be recorded as a decision of the Combined Policy Committee.|$|E
